<item>
            <title>[LU-17557] accessing non-existing inode turns fs read-only on 5.14</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17557</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;because all inodes are treated special since &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13166&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_812b: FAIL: lfs quota should succeed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13166&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13166&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; landing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
[   38.925720] LDISKFS-fs error (device dm-0): osd_iget2:520: inode #176: comm mdt00_001: iget: special inode unallocated
[   38.925723] Aborting journal on device dm-0-8.
[   38.925752] LustreError: 6725:0:(osd_handler.c:1886:osd_trans_commit_cb()) transaction @0xffff9a5be5fcf200 commit error: 2
[   38.925799] LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): Remounting filesystem read-only
&lt;/pre&gt;
